-- Mechel, Rosneft and Norilsk Nickel: Russian Equities Preview
-- B y   S t e p h e n   B i e r m a n
-- 2010-09-23T02:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-23/mechel-rosneft-and-norilsk-nickel-russian-equities-preview.html
The following companies may be
active in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
share prices are from the previous close of trading in Moscow.  The 30-stock Micex Index lost 0.2 percent to 1,431.21 at
the close in Moscow. The dollar-denominated RTS Index fell 0.1
percent to 1,477.01.  OAO Mechel  (MTLR RX): Russia’s largest producer of coal for
steelmaking said its Romanian steel units were in compliance
with the European Commission. Mechel fell 0.5 percent to 749
rubles.  OAO Rosneft  (ROSN RX): Crude oil declined, giving up
earlier gains, after a U.S. government report showed an
unexpected increase in inventories. Russia’s largest crude
producer fell 1.1 percent to 201.17 rubles.  OAO GMK Norilsk Nickel  (GMKN RX): Copper futures for
December delivery rose to a five-month high as the slumping
dollar boosted the appeal of commodities as alternative
investments. Norilsk, Russia’s largest miner, rose 0.3 percent
to 4,979.78 rubles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Stephen Bierman  in Moscow 
